name: Foy Yin Vegetarian Food

reviews.text:
Breakfast: $3 for vegetarian noodle set.
Went at 630am weekday. Noodles are bland. Fried goose is not as crispy. Other ingredients are decent. Portion is also decent. Green chilli and chilli is not self service. Need to be requested.
Overall very average.

Dinner: $4 for duck rice and $1.50 for soup.
Duck mock meat is braised. The chilli is nice. Rice has hint of herbal taste. The soup has generous ingredients such as corn, fungus tofu, carrot etc. soup taste good.

Dinner:$4 for hokkien mee. The taste is Abit bland, taste more like "seafood beehoon". More bee Hoon than yellow noodle. Ingredients are generous.

The sweet and sour pork rice is the crispy type and it's my favourite type of sweet sour pork. Their  mainland noodles ( Â§ßÈôÜÈù¢Ôºâ is very good as well. Their popiahs and mushroom rolls are very tasty. My first of many returns!

The best vegetarian duck rice in Singapore !
Very consistent have been coming here for years, another favourite is the Malaysian styles noodles fried fresh! Very friendly mother & son duo, super friendly and most importantly their sambal is stellar!

My first visit to this stall. Ordered the beehoon for only $3. I really really love it! It's hard to find this taste nowadays! It's nostalgic! Plus the crispy beancurd skin is the traditional kind (not those machine cut rectangular shaped ones), which makes it even more delicious üòÅ
Will come and try the PM menu too!

Delicious n cheap.

Visited here on 26/7/24.
Long time no come here.

The afternoon shift aunty said their new operating hrs starts from 6am - 830pm.
The 1st shift foods ready at 6am n end around 1pm +/-. The 2nd shift starts around 2pm till 830pm. I asked her which day the stall is close? She said they rest on the day after 1st, 15th n public holiday.
